The paper discusses the influence of emerging paradigms (Blockchain, IoT, and Artificial Intelligence) on cloud computing systems, which are typically studied in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential security and privacy concerns related to these emerging paradigms, which are studied in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a conceptual model for cloud futurology, which involves software engineering and system design, studied in the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the role of Artificial Intelligence in cloud computing, which is studied in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category is also relevant due to the potential security concerns related to the use of IoT devices in cloud computing systems.
